ly induced vection (see <xref ref-type="table" rid="table3-2041669517707768">Table 3</xref>). The rmANOVA revealed a significant main effect of display, <italic>F</italic>(3, 84)&#x02009;=&#x02009;5.026, <italic>p</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;.003, <inline-formula id="ilm8-2041669517707768"><mml:math id="mml-math8-2041669517707768"><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>&#x003b7;</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>p</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula><sup>&#x02009;</sup>=&#x02009;.152. Post&#x000a0;hoc comparisons showed significantly shorter vection duration for the projector compared with StreetLab (<italic>p</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;.049) and the three screens condition (<italic>p</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;.048).
